35template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
36void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::AeroCoeffsArray::allocate(int size) {
37 _size = size;
38 CD = new su2double[size];
39 CL = new su2double[size];
40 CSF = new su2double[size];
41 CEff = new su2double[size];
42 CFx = new su2double[size];
43 CFy = new su2double[size];
44 CFz = new su2double[size];
45 CMx = new su2double[size];
46 CMy = new su2double[size];
47 CMz = new su2double[size];
48 CoPx = new su2double[size];
49 CoPy = new su2double[size];
50 CoPz = new su2double[size];
51 CT = new su2double[size];
52 CQ = new su2double[size];
53 CMerit = new su2double[size];
54 setZero();
55}

77template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
78void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::AeroCoeffsArray::setZero(int i) {
79 CD[i] = CL[i] = CSF[i] = CEff[i] = 0.0;
80 CFx[i] = CFy[i] = CFz[i] = CMx[i] = 0.0;
81 CMy[i] = CMz[i] = CoPx[i] = CoPy[i] = 0.0;
82 CoPz[i] = CT[i] = CQ[i] = CMerit[i] = 0.0;
83}

85template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
86void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::Allocate(const CConfig& config) {
87 /*--- Define some auxiliar vector related with the residual ---*/
88
89 Residual_RMS.resize(nVar,0.0);
90 Residual_Max.resize(nVar,0.0);
91 Point_Max.resize(nVar,0);
92 Point_Max_Coord.resize(nVar,nDim) = su2double(0.0);
93
94 /*--- Define some auxiliar vector related with the undivided lapalacian computation ---*/
95
96 if ((config.GetKind_ConvNumScheme_Flow() == SPACE_CENTERED) && (MGLevel == MESH_0)) {
97 iPoint_UndLapl.resize(nPointDomain);
98 jPoint_UndLapl.resize(nPointDomain);
99 }
100
101 /*--- Initialize the solution and right hand side vectors for storing
102 the residuals and updating the solution (always needed even for
103 explicit schemes). ---*/
104
105 LinSysSol.Initialize(nPoint, nPointDomain, nVar, 0.0);
106 LinSysRes.Initialize(nPoint, nPointDomain, nVar, 0.0);
107
108 /*--- LinSysSol will always be init to 0. ---*/
109 System.SetxIsZero(true);
110
111 /*--- Store the value of the characteristic primitive variables at the boundaries ---*/
112
113 AllocVectorOfMatrices(nVertex, nPrimVar, CharacPrimVar);
114
115 /*--- Store the value of the Total Pressure at the inlet BC ---*/
116
117 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, Inlet_Ttotal);
118
119 /*--- Store the value of the Total Temperature at the inlet BC ---*/
120
121 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, Inlet_Ptotal);
122
123 /*--- Store the value of the Flow direction at the inlet BC ---*/
124
125 AllocVectorOfMatrices(nVertex, nDim, Inlet_FlowDir);
126
127 /*--- Force definition and coefficient arrays for all of the markers ---*/
128
129 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, CPressure);
130 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, CPressureTarget);
131
132 /*--- Non dimensional aerodynamic coefficients ---*/
133
134 InvCoeff.allocate(nMarker);
135 MntCoeff.allocate(nMarker);
136 ViscCoeff.allocate(nMarker);
137 SurfaceInvCoeff.allocate(config.GetnMarker_Monitoring());
138 SurfaceMntCoeff.allocate(config.GetnMarker_Monitoring());
139 SurfaceViscCoeff.allocate(config.GetnMarker_Monitoring());
140 SurfaceCoeff.allocate(config.GetnMarker_Monitoring());
141
142 /*--- Heat flux coefficients. ---*/
143
144 HF_Visc.resize(nMarker,0.0);
145 MaxHF_Visc.resize(nMarker,0.0);
146
147 Surface_HF_Visc.resize(config.GetnMarker_Monitoring());
148 Surface_MaxHF_Visc.resize(config.GetnMarker_Monitoring());
149
150 /*--- Supersonic coefficients ---*/
151
152 CNearFieldOF_Inv.resize(nMarker,0.0);
153
154 /*--- Initializate quantities for SlidingMesh Interface ---*/
155
156 SlidingState.resize(nMarker);
157 SlidingStateNodes.resize(nMarker);
158
159 for (unsigned long iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker; iMarker++) {
160 if (config.GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == FLUID_INTERFACE) {
161 SlidingState[iMarker].resize(nVertex[iMarker], nPrimVar+1) = nullptr;
162 SlidingStateNodes[iMarker].resize(nVertex[iMarker],0);
163 }
164 }
165
166 /*--- Heat flux in all the markers ---*/
167
168 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, HeatFlux);
169 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, HeatFluxTarget);
170
171 /*--- Y plus in all the markers ---*/
172
173 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, YPlus);
174
175 /*--- U Tau in all the markers ---*/
176
177 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, UTau);
178
179 /*--- wall eddy viscosity in all the markers ---*/
180
181 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, EddyViscWall);
182
183 /*--- Skin friction in all the markers ---*/
184
185 AllocVectorOfMatrices(nVertex, nDim, CSkinFriction);
186
187 /*--- Wall Shear Stress in all the markers ---*/
188
189 AllocVectorOfVectors(nVertex, WallShearStress);
190
191 /*--- Store the values of the temperature and the heat flux density at the boundaries,
192 used for coupling with a solid donor cell ---*/
193 constexpr auto nHeatConjugateVar = 4u;
194 AllocVectorOfMatrices(nVertex, nHeatConjugateVar, HeatConjugateVar, config.GetTemperature_FreeStreamND());
195
196 if (MGLevel == MESH_0) {
197 auto nSolidVertex = nVertex;
198 for (unsigned long iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker; iMarker++)
199 if (!config.GetSolid_Wall(iMarker))
200 nSolidVertex[iMarker] = 0;
201
202 AllocVectorOfMatrices(nSolidVertex, nDim, VertexTraction);
203
204 if (config.GetDiscrete_Adjoint()) AllocVectorOfMatrices(nSolidVertex, nDim, VertexTractionAdjoint);
205 }
206
207 /*--- Initialize the BGS residuals in FSI problems. ---*/
208 if (config.GetMultizone_Residual()) {
209 Residual_BGS.resize(nVar,1.0);
210 Residual_Max_BGS.resize(nVar,1.0);
211 Point_Max_BGS.resize(nVar,0);
212 Point_Max_Coord_BGS.resize(nVar,nDim) = su2double(0.0);
213 }
214}

216template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
217void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::AllocateTerribleLegacyTemporaryVariables() {
218 /*--- Define some auxiliary vectors related to the residual ---*/
219
220 Residual = new su2double[nVar]();
221 Res_Conv = new su2double[nVar]();
222 Res_Visc = new su2double[nVar]();
223 Res_Sour = new su2double[nVar]();
224
225 /*--- Define some auxiliary vectors related to the solution ---*/
226
227 Solution = new su2double[nVar]();
228 Solution_i = new su2double[nVar]();
229 Solution_j = new su2double[nVar]();
230
231 /*--- Define some auxiliary vectors related to the geometry ---*/
232
233 Vector = new su2double[nDim]();
234 Vector_i = new su2double[nDim]();
235 Vector_j = new su2double[nDim]();
236
237 /*--- Jacobian temporaries. ---*/
238
239 Jacobian_i = new su2double*[nVar];
240 Jacobian_j = new su2double*[nVar];
241 for (auto iVar = 0u; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
242 Jacobian_i[iVar] = new su2double[nVar];
243 Jacobian_j[iVar] = new su2double[nVar];
244 }
245}

247template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
248void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::CommunicateInitialState(CGeometry* geometry, const CConfig* config) {
249 /*--- Define solver parameters needed for execution of destructor ---*/
250
251 space_centered = (config->GetKind_ConvNumScheme_Flow() == SPACE_CENTERED);
252 euler_implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
253 least_squares = (config->GetKind_Gradient_Method() == WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES);
254
255 /*--- Communicate and store volume and the number of neighbors for
256 any dual CVs that lie on on periodic markers. ---*/
257
258 for (unsigned short iPeriodic = 1; iPeriodic <= config->GetnMarker_Periodic() / 2; iPeriodic++) {
259 InitiatePeriodicComms(geometry, config, iPeriodic, PERIODIC_VOLUME);
260 CompletePeriodicComms(geometry, config, iPeriodic, PERIODIC_VOLUME);
261 InitiatePeriodicComms(geometry, config, iPeriodic, PERIODIC_NEIGHBORS);
262 CompletePeriodicComms(geometry, config, iPeriodic, PERIODIC_NEIGHBORS);
263 }
264 SetImplicitPeriodic(euler_implicit);
265 if (MGLevel == MESH_0) SetRotatePeriodic(true);
266
267 /*--- Perform the MPI communication of the solution ---*/
268
269 InitiateComms(geometry, config, SOLUTION);
270 CompleteComms(geometry, config, SOLUTION);
271
272 /*--- Store the initial CFL number for all grid points. ---*/
273
274 const auto CFL = config->GetCFL(MGLevel);
275 for (auto iPoint = 0ul; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint++) {
276 nodes->SetLocalCFL(iPoint, CFL);
277 }
278 Min_CFL_Local = CFL;
279 Max_CFL_Local = CFL;
280 Avg_CFL_Local = CFL;
281}

283template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
284void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::HybridParallelInitialization(const CConfig& config, CGeometry& geometry) {
285#ifdef HAVE_OMP
286 /*--- Get the edge coloring. If the expected parallel efficiency becomes too low setup the
287 * reducer strategy. Where one loop is performed over edges followed by a point loop to
288 * sum the fluxes for each cell and set the diagonal of the system matrix. ---*/
289
290 su2double parallelEff = 1.0;
291
292#ifdef CODI_REVERSE_TYPE
293 /*--- For the discrete adjoint, the reducer strategy is costly. Prefer coloring, possibly with reduced edge color
294 * group size. Find the maximum edge color group size that yields an efficient coloring. Also, allow larger numbers
295 * of colors. ---*/
296 const bool relax = config.GetEdgeColoringRelaxDiscAdj();
297 const auto& coloring = geometry.GetEdgeColoring(&parallelEff, relax);
298#else
299 const auto& coloring = geometry.GetEdgeColoring(&parallelEff);
300#endif
301
302 /*--- The decision to use the strategy is local to each rank. ---*/
303 ReducerStrategy = parallelEff < COLORING_EFF_THRESH;
304
305 /*--- When using the reducer force a single color to reduce the color loop overhead. ---*/
306 if (ReducerStrategy && (coloring.getOuterSize() > 1)) geometry.SetNaturalEdgeColoring();
307
308 if (!coloring.empty()) {
309 /*--- If the reducer strategy is used we are not constrained by group
310 * size as we have no other edge loops in the Euler/NS solvers. ---*/
311 auto groupSize = ReducerStrategy ? 1ul : geometry.GetEdgeColorGroupSize();
312 auto nColor = coloring.getOuterSize();
313 EdgeColoring.reserve(nColor);
314
315 for (auto iColor = 0ul; iColor < nColor; ++iColor)
316 EdgeColoring.emplace_back(coloring.innerIdx(iColor), coloring.getNumNonZeros(iColor), groupSize);
317 }
318
319 /*--- If the reducer strategy is not being forced (by EDGE_COLORING_GROUP_SIZE=0) print some messages. ---*/
320 if (config.GetEdgeColoringGroupSize() != 1 << 30) {
321 su2double minEff = 1.0;
322 SU2_MPI::Reduce(&parallelEff, &minEff, 1, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MIN, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
323
324 int tmp = ReducerStrategy, numRanksUsingReducer = 0;
325 SU2_MPI::Reduce(&tmp, &numRanksUsingReducer, 1, MPI_INT, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
326
327 if (minEff < COLORING_EFF_THRESH) {
328 cout << "WARNING: On " << numRanksUsingReducer << " MPI ranks the coloring efficiency was less than "
329 << COLORING_EFF_THRESH << " (min value was " << minEff << ").\n"
330 << " Those ranks will now use a fallback strategy, better performance may be possible\n"
331 << " with a different value of config option EDGE_COLORING_GROUP_SIZE (default 512)."
332#ifdef HAVE_OPDI
333 << "\n The memory usage of the discrete adjoint solver is higher when using the fallback."
334#endif
335 << endl;
336 } else {
337 if (SU2_MPI::GetRank() == MASTER_NODE) {
338 cout << "All ranks use edge coloring." << endl;
339 }
340 }
341
342 const su2double coloredParallelEff = ReducerStrategy ? 1.0 : parallelEff;
343 su2double minColoredParallelEff = 1.0;
344 SU2_MPI::Reduce(&coloredParallelEff, &minColoredParallelEff, 1, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MIN, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
345
346 const unsigned long coloredNumColors = ReducerStrategy ? 0 : coloring.getOuterSize();
347 unsigned long maxColoredNumColors = 0;
348 SU2_MPI::Reduce(&coloredNumColors, &maxColoredNumColors, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MAX, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
349
350 const unsigned long coloredEdgeColorGroupSize = ReducerStrategy ? 1 << 30 : geometry.GetEdgeColorGroupSize();
351 unsigned long minColoredEdgeColorGroupSize = 1 << 30;
352 SU2_MPI::Reduce(&coloredEdgeColorGroupSize, &minColoredEdgeColorGroupSize, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MIN, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
353
354 if (SU2_MPI::GetRank() == MASTER_NODE && numRanksUsingReducer != SU2_MPI::GetSize()) {
355 cout << "Among the ranks that use edge coloring,\n"
356 << " the minimum efficiency is " << minColoredParallelEff << ",\n"
357 << " the maximum number of colors is " << maxColoredNumColors << ",\n"
358 << " the minimum edge color group size is " << minColoredEdgeColorGroupSize << "." << endl;
359 }
360 }
361
362 if (ReducerStrategy) EdgeFluxes.Initialize(geometry.GetnEdge(), geometry.GetnEdge(), nVar, nullptr);
363
364 omp_chunk_size = computeStaticChunkSize(nPoint, omp_get_max_threads(), OMP_MAX_SIZE);
365#else
366 EdgeColoring[0] = DummyGridColor<>(geometry.GetnEdge());
367#endif
368}

381template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
382void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::SetPrimitive_Gradient_GG(CGeometry* geometry, const CConfig* config,
383 bool reconstruction) {
384 const auto& primitives = nodes->GetPrimitive();
385 auto& gradient = reconstruction ? nodes->GetGradient_Reconstruction() : nodes->GetGradient_Primitive();
386 const auto comm = reconstruction? PRIMITIVE_GRAD_REC : PRIMITIVE_GRADIENT;
387 const auto commPer = reconstruction? PERIODIC_PRIM_GG_R : PERIODIC_PRIM_GG;
388
389 computeGradientsGreenGauss(this, comm, commPer, *geometry, *config, primitives, 0, nPrimVarGrad, gradient);
390}

392template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
393void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::SetPrimitive_Gradient_LS(CGeometry* geometry, const CConfig* config,
394 bool reconstruction) {
395 /*--- Set a flag for unweighted or weighted least-squares. ---*/
396 bool weighted;
397 PERIODIC_QUANTITIES commPer;
398
399 if (reconstruction) {
400 weighted = (config->GetKind_Gradient_Method_Recon() == WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES);
401 commPer = weighted? PERIODIC_PRIM_LS_R : PERIODIC_PRIM_ULS_R;
402 }
403 else {
404 weighted = (config->GetKind_Gradient_Method() == WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES);
405 commPer = weighted? PERIODIC_PRIM_LS : PERIODIC_PRIM_ULS;
406 }
407
408 const auto& primitives = nodes->GetPrimitive();
409 auto& rmatrix = nodes->GetRmatrix();
410 auto& gradient = reconstruction ? nodes->GetGradient_Reconstruction() : nodes->GetGradient_Primitive();
411 const auto comm = reconstruction? PRIMITIVE_GRAD_REC : PRIMITIVE_GRADIENT;
412
413 computeGradientsLeastSquares(this, comm, commPer, *geometry, *config, weighted,
414 primitives, 0, nPrimVarGrad, gradient, rmatrix);
415}

430template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
431void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::Viscous_Residual_impl(unsigned long iEdge, CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container,
432 CNumerics *numerics, CConfig *config) {
433
434 const bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
435 const bool tkeNeeded = (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == TURB_MODEL::SST);
436
437 CVariable* turbNodes = nullptr;
438 if (tkeNeeded) turbNodes = solver_container[TURB_SOL]->GetNodes();
439
440 /*--- Points, coordinates and normal vector in edge ---*/
441
442 auto iPoint = geometry->edges->GetNode(iEdge,0);
443 auto jPoint = geometry->edges->GetNode(iEdge,1);
444
445 numerics->SetCoord(geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint),
446 geometry->nodes->GetCoord(jPoint));
447
448 numerics->SetNormal(geometry->edges->GetNormal(iEdge));
449
450 /*--- Primitive and secondary variables. ---*/
451
452 numerics->SetPrimitive(nodes->GetPrimitive(iPoint),
453 nodes->GetPrimitive(jPoint));
454
455 numerics->SetSecondary(nodes->GetSecondary(iPoint),
456 nodes->GetSecondary(jPoint));
457
458 /*--- Gradients. ---*/
459
460 numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(nodes->GetGradient_Primitive(iPoint),
461 nodes->GetGradient_Primitive(jPoint));
462
463 /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy. ---*/
464
465 if (tkeNeeded)
466 numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(turbNodes->GetSolution(iPoint,0),
467 turbNodes->GetSolution(jPoint,0));
468
469 /*--- Wall shear stress values (wall functions) ---*/
470
471 numerics->SetTau_Wall(nodes->GetTau_Wall(iPoint),
472 nodes->GetTau_Wall(jPoint));
473
474 /*--- Compute and update residual ---*/
475
476 auto residual = numerics->ComputeResidual(config);
477
478 if (ReducerStrategy) {
479 EdgeFluxes.SubtractBlock(iEdge, residual);
480 if (implicit)
481 Jacobian.UpdateBlocksSub(iEdge, residual.jacobian_i, residual.jacobian_j);
482 }
483 else {
484 LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, residual);
485 LinSysRes.AddBlock(jPoint, residual);
486
487 if (implicit)
488 Jacobian.UpdateBlocksSub(iEdge, iPoint, jPoint, residual.jacobian_i, residual.jacobian_j);
489 }
490
491}

493template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
494void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::ComputeVerificationError(CGeometry* geometry, CConfig* config) {
495
496 /*--- The errors only need to be computed on the finest grid. ---*/
497 if (MGLevel != MESH_0) return;
498
499 /*--- If this is a verification case, we can compute the global
500 error metrics by using the difference between the local error
501 and the known solution at each DOF. This is then collected into
502 RMS (L2) and maximum (Linf) global error norms. From these
503 global measures, one can compute the order of accuracy. ---*/
504
505 bool write_heads =
506 ((((config->GetInnerIter() % (config->GetScreen_Wrt_Freq(2) * 40)) == 0) && (config->GetInnerIter() != 0)) ||
507 (config->GetInnerIter() == 1));
508 if (!write_heads) return;
509
510 BEGIN_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS {
511
512 /*--- Check if there actually is an exact solution for this
513 verification case, if computed at all. ---*/
514 if (VerificationSolution && VerificationSolution->ExactSolutionKnown()) {
515 /*--- Get the physical time if necessary. ---*/
516 su2double time = 0.0;
517 if (config->GetTime_Marching() != TIME_MARCHING::STEADY) time = config->GetPhysicalTime();
518
519 /*--- Reset the global error measures to zero. ---*/
520 for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
521 VerificationSolution->SetError_RMS(iVar, 0.0);
522 VerificationSolution->SetError_Max(iVar, 0.0, 0);
523 }
524
525 /*--- Loop over all owned points. ---*/
526 for (unsigned long iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
527 /* Set the pointers to the coordinates and solution of this DOF. */
528 const su2double* coor = geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint);
529 su2double* solDOF = nodes->GetSolution(iPoint);
530
531 /* Get local error from the verification solution class. */
532 vector<su2double> error(nVar, 0.0);
533 VerificationSolution->GetLocalError(coor, time, solDOF, error.data());
534
535 /* Increment the global error measures */
536 for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
537 VerificationSolution->AddError_RMS(iVar, error[iVar] * error[iVar]);
538 VerificationSolution->AddError_Max(iVar, fabs(error[iVar]), geometry->nodes->GetGlobalIndex(iPoint),
539 geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint));
540 }
541 }
542
543 /* Finalize the calculation of the global error measures. */
544 VerificationSolution->SetVerificationError(geometry->GetGlobal_nPointDomain(), config);
545
546 /*--- Screen output of the error metrics. This can be improved
547 once the new output classes are in place. ---*/
548
549 PrintVerificationError(config);
550 }
551
552 }
553 END_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS
554}

556template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
557void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::ComputeUnderRelaxationFactor(const CConfig* config) {
558 /* Loop over the solution update given by relaxing the linear
559 system for this nonlinear iteration. */
560
561 const su2double allowableRatio = 0.2;
562
563 SU2_OMP_FOR_STAT(omp_chunk_size)
564 for (unsigned long iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
565 su2double localUnderRelaxation = 1.0;
566
567 for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
568 /* We impose a limit on the maximum percentage that the
569 density and energy can change over a nonlinear iteration. */
570
571 if ((iVar == 0) || (iVar == nVar - 1)) {
572 const unsigned long index = iPoint * nVar + iVar;
573 su2double ratio = fabs(LinSysSol[index]) / (fabs(nodes->GetSolution(iPoint, iVar)) + EPS);
574 if (ratio > allowableRatio) {
575 localUnderRelaxation = min(allowableRatio / ratio, localUnderRelaxation);
576 }
577 }
578 }
579
580 /* Threshold the relaxation factor in the event that there is
581 a very small value. This helps avoid catastrophic crashes due
582 to non-realizable states by canceling the update. */
583
584 if (localUnderRelaxation < 1e-10) localUnderRelaxation = 0.0;
585
586 /* Store the under-relaxation factor for this point. */
587
588 nodes->SetUnderRelaxation(iPoint, localUnderRelaxation);
589 }
590 END_SU2_OMP_FOR
591}

593template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
594void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::ImplicitEuler_Iteration(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver**, CConfig *config) {
595
596 PrepareImplicitIteration(geometry, nullptr, config);
597
598 /*--- Solve or smooth the linear system. ---*/
599
600 SU2_OMP_FOR_(schedule(static,OMP_MIN_SIZE) SU2_NOWAIT)
601 for (unsigned long iPoint = nPointDomain; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint++) {
602 LinSysRes.SetBlock_Zero(iPoint);
603 LinSysSol.SetBlock_Zero(iPoint);
604 }
605 END_SU2_OMP_FOR
606
607 auto iter = System.Solve(Jacobian, LinSysRes, LinSysSol, geometry, config);
608
609 BEGIN_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS {
610 SetIterLinSolver(iter);
611 SetResLinSolver(System.GetResidual());
612 }
613 END_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS
614
615 CompleteImplicitIteration(geometry, nullptr, config);
616}
617
618template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
619void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::ComputeVorticityAndStrainMag(const CConfig& config, const CGeometry *geometry, unsigned short iMesh) {
620
621 auto& StrainMag = nodes->GetStrainMag();
622
623 ompMasterAssignBarrier(StrainMag_Max,0.0, Omega_Max,0.0);
624
625 su2double strainMax = 0.0, omegaMax = 0.0;
626
627 SU2_OMP_FOR_STAT(omp_chunk_size)
628 for (unsigned long iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPoint; ++iPoint) {
629
630 const auto VelocityGradient = nodes->GetVelocityGradient(iPoint);
631 auto Vorticity = nodes->GetVorticity(iPoint);
632
633 /*--- Vorticity ---*/
634
635 Vorticity[0] = 0.0;
636 Vorticity[1] = 0.0;
637 Vorticity[2] = VelocityGradient(1,0)-VelocityGradient(0,1);
638
639 if (nDim == 3) {
640 Vorticity[0] = VelocityGradient(2,1)-VelocityGradient(1,2);
641 Vorticity[1] = -(VelocityGradient(2,0)-VelocityGradient(0,2));
642 }
643
644 /*--- Strain Magnitude ---*/
645
646 const su2double vy = nodes->GetVelocity(iPoint, 1);
647 const su2double y = geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint, 1);
648 AD::StartPreacc();
649 AD::SetPreaccIn(VelocityGradient, nDim, nDim);
650 AD::SetPreaccIn(vy, y);
651
652 StrainMag(iPoint) = 0.0;
653
654 /*--- Add diagonal part ---*/
655
656 for (unsigned long iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
657 StrainMag(iPoint) += pow(VelocityGradient(iDim, iDim), 2);
658 }
659 if (config.GetAxisymmetric() && y > EPS) {
660 StrainMag(iPoint) += pow(vy / y, 2);
661 }
662
663 /*--- Add off diagonals ---*/
664
665 StrainMag(iPoint) += 2.0*pow(0.5*(VelocityGradient(0,1) + VelocityGradient(1,0)), 2);
666
667 if (nDim == 3) {
668 StrainMag(iPoint) += 2.0*pow(0.5*(VelocityGradient(0,2) + VelocityGradient(2,0)), 2);
669 StrainMag(iPoint) += 2.0*pow(0.5*(VelocityGradient(1,2) + VelocityGradient(2,1)), 2);
670 }
671
672 StrainMag(iPoint) = sqrt(2.0*StrainMag(iPoint));
673 AD::SetPreaccOut(StrainMag(iPoint));
674
675 /*--- Max is not differentiable, so we not register them for preacc. ---*/
676 strainMax = max(strainMax, StrainMag(iPoint));
677 omegaMax = max(omegaMax, GeometryToolbox::Norm(3, Vorticity));
678
679 AD::EndPreacc();
680 }
681 END_SU2_OMP_FOR
682
683 if ((iMesh == MESH_0) && (config.GetComm_Level() == COMM_FULL)) {
684 SU2_OMP_CRITICAL {
685 StrainMag_Max = max(StrainMag_Max, strainMax);
686 Omega_Max = max(Omega_Max, omegaMax);
687 }
688 END_SU2_OMP_CRITICAL
689
690 BEGIN_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS
691 {
692 su2double MyOmega_Max = Omega_Max;
693 su2double MyStrainMag_Max = StrainMag_Max;
694
695 SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&MyStrainMag_Max, &StrainMag_Max, 1, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MAX, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
696 SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&MyOmega_Max, &Omega_Max, 1, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MAX, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
697 }
698 END_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS
699 }
700
701}

703template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
704void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::SetInletAtVertex(const su2double* val_inlet, unsigned short iMarker,
705 unsigned long iVertex) {
706 /*--- Alias positions within inlet file for readability ---*/
707
708 unsigned short T_position = nDim;
709 unsigned short P_position = nDim + 1;
710 unsigned short FlowDir_position = nDim + 2;
711
712 /*--- Note that it is not necessary anymore to use normalized normals for the inlet velocity ---*/
713
714
715 /*--- Store the values in our inlet data structures. ---*/
716
717 Inlet_Ttotal[iMarker][iVertex] = val_inlet[T_position];
718 Inlet_Ptotal[iMarker][iVertex] = val_inlet[P_position];
719 for (unsigned short iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
720 Inlet_FlowDir[iMarker][iVertex][iDim] = val_inlet[FlowDir_position + iDim];
721 }
722}
723
724template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
725su2double CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::GetInletAtVertex(su2double* val_inlet, unsigned long val_inlet_point,
726 unsigned short val_kind_marker, string val_marker,
727 const CGeometry* geometry, const CConfig* config) const {
728 /*--- Local variables ---*/
729
730 unsigned short iMarker, iDim;
731 unsigned long iPoint, iVertex;
732 su2double Area = 0.0;
733 su2double Normal[3] = {0.0, 0.0, 0.0};
734
735 /*--- Alias positions within inlet file for readability ---*/
736
737 unsigned short T_position = nDim;
738 unsigned short P_position = nDim + 1;
739 unsigned short FlowDir_position = nDim + 2;
740
741 if (val_kind_marker == INLET_FLOW) {
742 for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
743 if ((config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == INLET_FLOW) &&
744 (config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker) == val_marker)) {
745 for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
746 iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
747
748 if (iPoint == val_inlet_point) {
749 /*-- Compute boundary face area for this vertex. ---*/
750
751 geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
752 Area = GeometryToolbox::Norm(nDim, Normal);
753
754 /*--- Access and store the inlet variables for this vertex. ---*/
755
756 val_inlet[T_position] = Inlet_Ttotal[iMarker][iVertex];
757 val_inlet[P_position] = Inlet_Ptotal[iMarker][iVertex];
758 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
759 val_inlet[FlowDir_position + iDim] = Inlet_FlowDir[iMarker][iVertex][iDim];
760 }
761
762 /*--- Exit once we find the point. ---*/
763
764 return Area;
765 }
766 }
767 }
768 }
769 }
770
771 /*--- If we don't find a match, then the child point is not on the
772 current inlet boundary marker. Return zero area so this point does
773 not contribute to the restriction operator and continue. ---*/
774
775 return Area;
776}

778template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
779void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::SetUniformInlet(const CConfig* config, unsigned short iMarker) {
780 if (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == INLET_FLOW) {
781 string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker);
782 su2double p_total = config->GetInlet_Ptotal(Marker_Tag);
783 su2double t_total = config->GetInlet_Ttotal(Marker_Tag);
784 auto flow_dir = config->GetInlet_FlowDir(Marker_Tag);
785
786 for (unsigned long iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
787 Inlet_Ttotal[iMarker][iVertex] = t_total;
788 Inlet_Ptotal[iMarker][iVertex] = p_total;
789 for (unsigned short iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Inlet_FlowDir[iMarker][iVertex][iDim] = flow_dir[iDim];
790 }
791
792 } else {
793 /*--- For now, non-inlets just get set to zero. In the future, we
794 can do more customization for other boundary types here. ---*/
795 for (unsigned long iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
796 Inlet_Ttotal[iMarker][iVertex] = 0.0;
797 Inlet_Ptotal[iMarker][iVertex] = 0.0;
798 for (unsigned short iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Inlet_FlowDir[iMarker][iVertex][iDim] = 0.0;
799 }
800 }

803template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
804void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::LoadRestart_impl(CGeometry **geometry, CSolver ***solver, CConfig *config, int iter,
805 bool update_geo, su2double* SolutionRestart,
806 unsigned short nVar_Restart) {
807 /*--- Restart the solution from file information ---*/
808
809 const string restart_filename = config->GetFilename(config->GetSolution_FileName(), "", iter);
810 const bool static_fsi = ((config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::STEADY) && config->GetFSI_Simulation());
811
812 /*--- To make this routine safe to call in parallel most of it can only be executed by one thread. ---*/
813 BEGIN_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS {
814
815 if (nVar_Restart == 0) nVar_Restart = nVar;
816
817 /*--- Skip coordinates ---*/
818
819 unsigned short skipVars = nDim;
820
821 /*--- Read the restart data from either an ASCII or binary SU2 file. ---*/
822
823 if (config->GetRead_Binary_Restart()) {
824 Read_SU2_Restart_Binary(geometry[MESH_0], config, restart_filename);
825 } else {
826 Read_SU2_Restart_ASCII(geometry[MESH_0], config, restart_filename);
827 }
828
829 bool steady_restart = config->GetSteadyRestart();
830 if (update_geo && dynamic_grid) {
831 auto notFound = fields.end();
832 if (find(fields.begin(), notFound, string("\"Grid_Velocity_x\"")) == notFound) {
833 if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
834 cout << "\nWARNING: The restart file does not contain grid velocities, these will be set to zero.\n" << endl;
835 steady_restart = true;
836 }
837 }
838
839 /*--- Load data from the restart into correct containers. ---*/
840
841 unsigned long counter = 0;
842 for (auto iPoint_Global = 0ul; iPoint_Global < geometry[MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain(); iPoint_Global++) {
843
844 /*--- Retrieve local index. If this node from the restart file lives
845 on the current processor, we will load and instantiate the vars. ---*/
846
847 const auto iPoint_Local = geometry[MESH_0]->GetGlobal_to_Local_Point(iPoint_Global);
848
849 if (iPoint_Local > -1) {
850
851 /*--- We need to store this point's data, so jump to the correct
852 offset in the buffer of data from the restart file and load it. ---*/
853
854 auto index = counter * Restart_Vars[1] + skipVars;
855
856 if (SolutionRestart == nullptr) {
857 for (auto iVar = 0u; iVar < nVar_Restart; iVar++)
858 nodes->SetSolution(iPoint_Local, iVar, Restart_Data[index+iVar]);
859 }
860 else {
861 /*--- Used as buffer, allows defaults for nVar > nVar_Restart. ---*/
862 for (auto iVar = 0u; iVar < nVar_Restart; iVar++)
863 SolutionRestart[iVar] = Restart_Data[index + iVar];
864 nodes->SetSolution(iPoint_Local, SolutionRestart);
865 }
866
867 /*--- For dynamic meshes, read in and store the
868 grid coordinates and grid velocities for each node. ---*/
869
870 if (dynamic_grid && update_geo) {
871
872 /*--- Read in the next 2 or 3 variables which are the grid velocities ---*/
873 /*--- If we are restarting the solution from a previously computed static calculation (no grid movement) ---*/
874 /*--- the grid velocities are set to 0. This is useful for FSI computations ---*/
875
876 /*--- Rewind the index to retrieve the Coords. ---*/
877 index = counter * Restart_Vars[1];
878 const auto* Coord = &Restart_Data[index];
879
880 su2double GridVel[MAXNDIM] = {0.0};
881 if (!steady_restart) {
882 /*--- Move the index forward to get the grid velocities. ---*/
883 index += skipVars + nVar_Restart + config->GetnTurbVar();
884 for (auto iDim = 0u; iDim < nDim; iDim++) { GridVel[iDim] = Restart_Data[index+iDim]; }
885 }
886
887 for (auto iDim = 0u; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
888 geometry[MESH_0]->nodes->SetCoord(iPoint_Local, iDim, Coord[iDim]);
889 geometry[MESH_0]->nodes->SetGridVel(iPoint_Local, iDim, GridVel[iDim]);
890 }
891 }
892
893 /*--- For static FSI problems, grid_movement is 0 but we need to read in and store the
894 grid coordinates for each node (but not the grid velocities, as there are none). ---*/
895
896 if (static_fsi && update_geo) {
897 /*--- Rewind the index to retrieve the Coords. ---*/
898 index = counter*Restart_Vars[1];
899 const auto* Coord = &Restart_Data[index];
900
901 for (auto iDim = 0u; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
902 geometry[MESH_0]->nodes->SetCoord(iPoint_Local, iDim, Coord[iDim]);
903 }
904 }
905
906 /*--- Increment the overall counter for how many points have been loaded. ---*/
907 counter++;
908 }
909 }
910
911 /*--- Detect a wrong solution file ---*/
912
913 if (counter != nPointDomain) {
914 SU2_MPI::Error(string("The solution file ") + restart_filename + string(" does not match with the mesh file.\n") +
915 string("This can be caused by empty lines at the end of the file."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
916 }
917 }
918 END_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS
919
920 /*--- Update the geometry for flows on deforming meshes. ---*/
921
922 if ((dynamic_grid || static_fsi) && update_geo) {
923
924 CGeometry::UpdateGeometry(geometry, config);
925
926 if (dynamic_grid) {
927 for (auto iMesh = 0u; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
928
929 /*--- Compute the grid velocities on the coarser levels. ---*/
930 if (iMesh) geometry[iMesh]->SetRestricted_GridVelocity(geometry[iMesh - 1]);
931 else {
932 geometry[MESH_0]->InitiateComms(geometry[MESH_0], config, GRID_VELOCITY);
933 geometry[MESH_0]->CompleteComms(geometry[MESH_0], config, GRID_VELOCITY);
934 }
935 }
936 }
937 }
938
939 /*--- Communicate the loaded solution on the fine grid before we transfer
940 it down to the coarse levels. We also call the preprocessing routine
941 on the fine level in order to have all necessary quantities updated,
942 especially if this is a turbulent simulation (eddy viscosity). ---*/
943
944 solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->InitiateComms(geometry[MESH_0], config, SOLUTION);
945 solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->CompleteComms(geometry[MESH_0], config, SOLUTION);
946
947 /*--- For turbulent/species simulations the flow preprocessing is done by the turbulence/species solver
948 * after it loads its variables (they are needed to compute flow primitives). In case turbulence and species, the
949 * species solver does all the Pre-/Postprocessing. ---*/
950 if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == TURB_MODEL::NONE &&
951 config->GetKind_Species_Model() == SPECIES_MODEL::NONE) {
952 solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->Preprocessing(geometry[MESH_0], solver[MESH_0], config, MESH_0, NO_RK_ITER, RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS, false);
953 }
954
955 /*--- Interpolate the solution down to the coarse multigrid levels ---*/
956
957 for (auto iMesh = 1u; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
958 MultigridRestriction(*geometry[iMesh - 1], solver[iMesh - 1][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(),
959 *geometry[iMesh], solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution());
960 solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->InitiateComms(geometry[iMesh], config, SOLUTION);
961 solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->CompleteComms(geometry[iMesh], config, SOLUTION);
962
963 if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == TURB_MODEL::NONE &&
964 config->GetKind_Species_Model() == SPECIES_MODEL::NONE) {
965 solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->Preprocessing(geometry[iMesh], solver[iMesh], config, iMesh, NO_RK_ITER, RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS, false);
966 }
967 }
968
969 /*--- Update the old geometry (coordinates n and n-1) in dual time-stepping strategy. ---*/
970 const bool dual_time = ((config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_1ST) ||
971 (config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND));
972 if (dual_time && config->GetGrid_Movement() && !config->GetDeform_Mesh() &&
973 (config->GetKind_GridMovement() != RIGID_MOTION)) {
974 Restart_OldGeometry(geometry[MESH_0], config);
975 }
976
977 /*--- Go back to single threaded execution. ---*/
978 BEGIN_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS
979 {
980 /*--- Delete the class memory that is used to load the restart. ---*/
981
982 Restart_Vars = decltype(Restart_Vars){};
983 Restart_Data = decltype(Restart_Data){};
984 }
985 END_SU2_OMP_SAFE_GLOBAL_ACCESS
986}
987
988template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
989void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::LoadRestart(CGeometry **geometry, CSolver ***solver,
990 CConfig *config, int iter, bool update_geo) {
991 LoadRestart_impl(geometry, solver, config, iter, update_geo);
992}
993
994template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
995void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::SetInitialCondition(CGeometry **geometry, CSolver ***solver_container,
996 CConfig *config, unsigned long TimeIter) {
997
998 const bool restart = (config->GetRestart() || config->GetRestart_Flow());
999 const bool rans = (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() != TURB_MODEL::NONE);
1000 const bool dual_time = ((config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_1ST) ||
1001 (config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND));
1002
1003 /*--- Start OpenMP parallel region. ---*/
1004
1005 SU2_OMP_PARALLEL {
1006
1007 unsigned long iPoint;
1008 unsigned short iMesh;
1009
1010 /*--- Check if a verification solution is to be computed. ---*/
1011 if ((VerificationSolution) && (TimeIter == 0) && !restart) {
1012
1013 /*--- Loop over the multigrid levels. ---*/
1014 for (iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
1015
1016 /*--- Loop over all grid points. ---*/
1017 SU2_OMP_FOR_STAT(omp_chunk_size)
1018 for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry[iMesh]->GetnPoint(); iPoint++) {
1019
1020 /* Set the pointers to the coordinates and solution of this DOF. */
1021 const su2double *coor = geometry[iMesh]->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint);
1022 su2double *solDOF = solver_container[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(iPoint);
1023
1024 /* Set the solution in this DOF to the initial condition provided by
1025 the verification solution class. This can be the exact solution,
1026 but this is not necessary. */
1027 VerificationSolution->GetInitialCondition(coor, solDOF);
1028 }
1029 END_SU2_OMP_FOR
1030 }
1031 }
1032
1033 /*--- The value of the solution for the first iteration of the dual time ---*/
1034
1035 if (dual_time && TimeIter == config->GetRestart_Iter()) {
1036 PushSolutionBackInTime(TimeIter, restart, rans, solver_container, geometry, config);
1037 }
1038
1039 }
1040 END_SU2_OMP_PARALLEL
1041
1042}
1043
1044template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
1045void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::PushSolutionBackInTime(unsigned long TimeIter, bool restart, bool rans,
1046 CSolver*** solver_container, CGeometry** geometry,
1047 CConfig* config) {
1048 /*--- Push back the initial condition to previous solution containers
1049 for a 1st-order restart or when simply intitializing to freestream. ---*/
1050
1051 for (unsigned short iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
1052 solver_container[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->Set_Solution_time_n();
1053 solver_container[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->Set_Solution_time_n1();
1054 if (rans) {
1055 solver_container[iMesh][TURB_SOL]->GetNodes()->Set_Solution_time_n();
1056 solver_container[iMesh][TURB_SOL]->GetNodes()->Set_Solution_time_n1();
1057 }
1058
1059 if (dynamic_grid) {
1060 geometry[iMesh]->nodes->SetVolume_n();
1061 geometry[iMesh]->nodes->SetVolume_nM1();
1062 }
1063
1064 if (config->GetGrid_Movement()) {
1065 geometry[iMesh]->nodes->SetCoord_n();
1066 geometry[iMesh]->nodes->SetCoord_n1();
1067 }
1068 }
1069
1070 if (restart && (config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND)) {
1071
1072 /*--- Load an additional restart file for a 2nd-order restart. ---*/
1073
1074 solver_container[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->LoadRestart(geometry, solver_container, config, TimeIter-1, true);
1075
1076 /*--- Load an additional restart file for the turbulence model. ---*/
1077 if (rans)
1078 solver_container[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->LoadRestart(geometry, solver_container, config, TimeIter-1, false);
1079
1080 /*--- Push back this new solution to time level N. ---*/
1081
1082 for (unsigned short iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
1083 solver_container[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->Set_Solution_time_n();
1084 if (rans) solver_container[iMesh][TURB_SOL]->GetNodes()->Set_Solution_time_n();
1085
1086 geometry[iMesh]->nodes->SetVolume_n();
1087 if (config->GetGrid_Movement()) geometry[iMesh]->nodes->SetCoord_n();
1088 }
1089 }
1090}
1091
1092template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
1093void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::BC_Sym_Plane(CGeometry* geometry, CSolver** solver_container, CNumerics* conv_numerics,
1094 CNumerics* visc_numerics, CConfig* config, unsigned short val_marker) {
1095 unsigned short iDim, iVar;
1096 unsigned long iVertex, iPoint;
1097
1098 bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
1099 bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
1100 bool preprocessed = false;
1101
1102 /*--- Allocation of variables necessary for convective fluxes. ---*/
1103 su2double Area, ProjVelocity_i, *V_reflected, *V_domain, Normal[MAXNDIM] = {0.0}, UnitNormal[MAXNDIM] = {0.0};
1104
1105 /*--- Allocation of variables necessary for viscous fluxes. ---*/
1106 su2double ProjGradient, ProjNormVelGrad, ProjTangVelGrad, TangentialNorm,
1107 Tangential[MAXNDIM] = {0.0}, GradNormVel[MAXNDIM] = {0.0}, GradTangVel[MAXNDIM] = {0.0};
1108
1109 /*--- Allocation of primitive gradient arrays for viscous fluxes. ---*/
1110 su2activematrix Grad_Reflected(nPrimVarGrad, nDim);
1111
1112 /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker. ---*/
1113
1114 SU2_OMP_FOR_DYN(OMP_MIN_SIZE)
1115 for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
1116 if (!preprocessed || geometry->bound_is_straight[val_marker] != true) {
1117 /*----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1118 /*--- Preprocessing: ---*/
1119 /*--- Compute the unit normal and (in case of viscous flow) a corresponding unit tangential ---*/
1120 /*--- to that normal. On a straight(2D)/plane(3D) boundary these two vectors are constant. ---*/
1121 /*--- This circumstance is checked in geometry->ComputeSurf_Straightness(...) and stored ---*/
1122 /*--- such that the recomputation does not occur for each node. On true symmetry planes, the ---*/
1123 /*--- normal is constant but this routines is used for Symmetry, Euler-Wall in inviscid flow ---*/
1124 /*--- and Euler Wall in viscous flow as well. In the latter curvy boundaries are likely to ---*/
1125 /*--- happen. In doubt, the conditional above which checks straightness can be thrown out ---*/
1126 /*--- such that the recomputation is done for each node (which comes with a tiny performance ---*/
1127 /*--- penalty). ---*/
1128 /*----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1129
1130 preprocessed = true;
1131
1132 /*--- Normal vector for a random vertex (zero) on this marker (negate for outward convention). ---*/
1133 geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
1134 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
1135
1136 /*--- Compute unit normal, to be used for unit tangential, projected velocity and velocity
1137 component gradients. ---*/
1138 Area = GeometryToolbox::Norm(nDim, Normal);
1139
1140 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) UnitNormal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim] / Area;
1141
1142 /*--- Preprocessing: Compute unit tangential, the direction is arbitrary as long as
1143 t*n=0 && |t|_2 = 1 ---*/
1144 if (viscous) {
1145 switch (nDim) {
1146 case 2: {
1147 Tangential[0] = -UnitNormal[1];
1148 Tangential[1] = UnitNormal[0];
1149 break;
1150 }
1151 case 3: {
1152 /*--- n = ai + bj + ck, if |b| > |c| ---*/
1153 if (abs(UnitNormal[1]) > abs(UnitNormal[2])) {
1154 /*--- t = bi + (c-a)j - bk ---*/
1155 Tangential[0] = UnitNormal[1];
1156 Tangential[1] = UnitNormal[2] - UnitNormal[0];
1157 Tangential[2] = -UnitNormal[1];
1158 } else {
1159 /*--- t = ci - cj + (b-a)k ---*/
1160 Tangential[0] = UnitNormal[2];
1161 Tangential[1] = -UnitNormal[2];
1162 Tangential[2] = UnitNormal[1] - UnitNormal[0];
1163 }
1164 /*--- Make it a unit vector. ---*/
1165 TangentialNorm = sqrt(pow(Tangential[0], 2) + pow(Tangential[1], 2) + pow(Tangential[2], 2));
1166 Tangential[0] = Tangential[0] / TangentialNorm;
1167 Tangential[1] = Tangential[1] / TangentialNorm;
1168 Tangential[2] = Tangential[2] / TangentialNorm;
1169 break;
1170 }
1171 } // switch
1172 } // if viscous
1173 } // if bound_is_straight
1174
1175 iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
1176
1177 /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e., not a halo node) ---*/
1178 if (geometry->nodes->GetDomain(iPoint)) {
1179 /*-------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1180 /*--- Step 1: For the convective fluxes, create a reflected state of the ---*/
1181 /*--- Primitive variables by copying all interior values to the ---*/
1182 /*--- reflected. Only the velocity is mirrored along the symmetry ---*/
1183 /*--- axis. Based on the Upwind_Residual routine. ---*/
1184 /*-------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1185
1186 /*--- Allocate the reflected state at the symmetry boundary. ---*/
1187 V_reflected = GetCharacPrimVar(val_marker, iVertex);
1188
1189 /*--- Grid movement ---*/
1190 if (dynamic_grid)
1191 conv_numerics->SetGridVel(geometry->nodes->GetGridVel(iPoint), geometry->nodes->GetGridVel(iPoint));
1192
1193 /*--- Normal vector for this vertex (negate for outward convention). ---*/
1194 geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
1195 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
1196 conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
1197
1198 /*--- Get current solution at this boundary node ---*/
1199 V_domain = nodes->GetPrimitive(iPoint);
1200
1201 /*--- Set the reflected state based on the boundary node. Scalars are copied and
1202 the velocity is mirrored along the symmetry boundary, i.e. the velocity in
1203 normal direction is substracted twice. ---*/
1204 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++) V_reflected[iVar] = nodes->GetPrimitive(iPoint, iVar);
1205
1206 /*--- Compute velocity in normal direction (ProjVelcity_i=(v*n)) und substract twice from
1207 velocity in normal direction: v_r = v - 2 (v*n)n ---*/
1208 ProjVelocity_i = nodes->GetProjVel(iPoint, UnitNormal);
1209
1210 /*--- Adjustment to v.n due to grid movement. ---*/
1211 if (dynamic_grid) {
1212 ProjVelocity_i -= GeometryToolbox::DotProduct(nDim, geometry->nodes->GetGridVel(iPoint), UnitNormal);
1213 }
1214
1215 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
1216 V_reflected[iDim + 1] = nodes->GetVelocity(iPoint, iDim) - 2.0 * ProjVelocity_i * UnitNormal[iDim];
1217
1218 /*--- Set Primitive and Secondary for numerics class. ---*/
1219 conv_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_reflected);
1220 conv_numerics->SetSecondary(nodes->GetSecondary(iPoint), nodes->GetSecondary(iPoint));
1221
1222 /*--- Compute the residual using an upwind scheme. ---*/
1223
1224 auto residual = conv_numerics->ComputeResidual(config);
1225
1226 /*--- Update residual value ---*/
1227 LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, residual);
1228
1229 /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration. ---*/
1230 if (implicit) {
1231 Jacobian.AddBlock2Diag(iPoint, residual.jacobian_i);
1232 }
1233
1234 if (viscous) {
1235 /*-------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1236 /*--- Step 2: The viscous fluxes of the Navier-Stokes equations depend on the ---*/
1237 /*--- Primitive variables and their gradients. The viscous numerics ---*/
1238 /*--- container is filled just as the convective numerics container, ---*/
1239 /*--- but the primitive gradients of the reflected state have to be ---*/
1240 /*--- determined additionally such that symmetry at the boundary is ---*/
1241 /*--- enforced. Based on the Viscous_Residual routine. ---*/
1242 /*-------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1243
1244 /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates. ---*/
1245 visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint), geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint));
1246 visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
1247
1248 /*--- Set the primitive and Secondary variables. ---*/
1249 visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_reflected);
1250 visc_numerics->SetSecondary(nodes->GetSecondary(iPoint), nodes->GetSecondary(iPoint));
1251
1252 /*--- For viscous Fluxes also the gradients of the primitives need to be determined.
1253 1. The gradients of scalars are mirrored along the sym plane just as velocity for the primitives
1254 2. The gradients of the velocity components need more attention, i.e. the gradient of the
1255 normal velocity in tangential direction is mirrored and the gradient of the tangential velocity in
1256 normal direction is mirrored. ---*/
1257
1258 /*--- Get gradients of primitives of boundary cell ---*/
1259 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVarGrad; iVar++)
1260 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
1261 Grad_Reflected[iVar][iDim] = nodes->GetGradient_Primitive(iPoint, iVar, iDim);
1262
1263 /*--- Reflect the gradients for all scalars including the velocity components.
1264 The gradients of the velocity components are set later with the
1265 correct values: grad(V)_r = grad(V) - 2 [grad(V)*n]n, V beeing any primitive ---*/
1266 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVarGrad; iVar++) {
1267 if (iVar == 0 || iVar > nDim) { // Exclude velocity component gradients
1268
1269 /*--- Compute projected part of the gradient in a dot product ---*/
1270 ProjGradient = 0.0;
1271 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) ProjGradient += Grad_Reflected[iVar][iDim] * UnitNormal[iDim];
1272
1273 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
1274 Grad_Reflected[iVar][iDim] = Grad_Reflected[iVar][iDim] - 2.0 * ProjGradient * UnitNormal[iDim];
1275 }
1276 }
1277
1278 /*--- Compute gradients of normal and tangential velocity:
1279 grad(v*n) = grad(v_x) n_x + grad(v_y) n_y (+ grad(v_z) n_z)
1280 grad(v*t) = grad(v_x) t_x + grad(v_y) t_y (+ grad(v_z) t_z) ---*/
1281 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nDim; iVar++) { // counts gradient components
1282 GradNormVel[iVar] = 0.0;
1283 GradTangVel[iVar] = 0.0;
1284 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) { // counts sum with unit normal/tangential
1285 GradNormVel[iVar] += Grad_Reflected[iDim + 1][iVar] * UnitNormal[iDim];
1286 GradTangVel[iVar] += Grad_Reflected[iDim + 1][iVar] * Tangential[iDim];
1287 }
1288 }
1289
1290 /*--- Refelect gradients in tangential and normal direction by substracting the normal/tangential
1291 component twice, just as done with velocity above.
1292 grad(v*n)_r = grad(v*n) - 2 {grad([v*n])*t}t
1293 grad(v*t)_r = grad(v*t) - 2 {grad([v*t])*n}n ---*/
1294 ProjNormVelGrad = 0.0;
1295 ProjTangVelGrad = 0.0;
1296 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
1297 ProjNormVelGrad += GradNormVel[iDim] * Tangential[iDim]; // grad([v*n])*t
1298 ProjTangVelGrad += GradTangVel[iDim] * UnitNormal[iDim]; // grad([v*t])*n
1299 }
1300
1301 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
1302 GradNormVel[iDim] = GradNormVel[iDim] - 2.0 * ProjNormVelGrad * Tangential[iDim];
1303 GradTangVel[iDim] = GradTangVel[iDim] - 2.0 * ProjTangVelGrad * UnitNormal[iDim];
1304 }
1305
1306 /*--- Transfer reflected gradients back into the Cartesian Coordinate system:
1307 grad(v_x)_r = grad(v*n)_r n_x + grad(v*t)_r t_x
1308 grad(v_y)_r = grad(v*n)_r n_y + grad(v*t)_r t_y
1309 ( grad(v_z)_r = grad(v*n)_r n_z + grad(v*t)_r t_z ) ---*/
1310 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nDim; iVar++) // loops over the velocity component gradients
1311 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) // loops over the entries of the above
1312 Grad_Reflected[iVar + 1][iDim] =
1313 GradNormVel[iDim] * UnitNormal[iVar] + GradTangVel[iDim] * Tangential[iVar];
1314
1315 /*--- Set the primitive gradients of the boundary and reflected state. ---*/
1316 visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(nodes->GetGradient_Primitive(iPoint), CMatrixView<su2double>(Grad_Reflected));
1317
1318 /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy. ---*/
1319 if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == TURB_MODEL::SST)
1320 visc_numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(solver_container[TURB_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(iPoint, 0),
1321 solver_container[TURB_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(iPoint, 0));
1322
1323 /*--- Compute and update residual. Note that the viscous shear stress tensor is computed in the
1324 following routine based upon the velocity-component gradients. ---*/
1325 auto residual = visc_numerics->ComputeResidual(config);
1326
1327 LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, residual);
1328
1329 /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration. ---*/
1330 if (implicit) Jacobian.SubtractBlock2Diag(iPoint, residual.jacobian_i);
1331 } // if viscous
1332 } // if GetDomain
1333 } // for iVertex
1334 END_SU2_OMP_FOR
1335
1336}

1338template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
1339void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::BC_Periodic(CGeometry* geometry, CSolver** solver_container, CNumerics* numerics,
1340 CConfig* config) {
1341 /*--- Complete residuals for periodic boundary conditions. We loop over
1342 the periodic BCs in matching pairs so that, in the event that there are
1343 adjacent periodic markers, the repeated points will have their residuals
1344 accumulated correctly during the communications. For implicit calculations,
1345 the Jacobians and linear system are also correctly adjusted here. ---*/
1346
1347 for (unsigned short iPeriodic = 1; iPeriodic <= config->GetnMarker_Periodic() / 2; iPeriodic++) {
1348 InitiatePeriodicComms(geometry, config, iPeriodic, PERIODIC_RESIDUAL);
1349 CompletePeriodicComms(geometry, config, iPeriodic, PERIODIC_RESIDUAL);
1350 }
1351}

1353template <class V, ENUM_REGIME FlowRegime>
1354void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, FlowRegime>::BC_Fluid_Interface(CGeometry* geometry, CSolver** solver_container,
1355 CNumerics* conv_numerics, CNumerics* visc_numerics,
1356 CConfig* config) {
1357 unsigned long iVertex, jVertex, iPoint, Point_Normal = 0;
1358 unsigned short iDim, iVar, jVar, iMarker, nDonorVertex;
1359
1360 bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
1361 bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
1362
1363 su2double Normal[MAXNDIM] = {0.0};
1364 su2double PrimVar_i[MAXNVAR] = {0.0};
1365 su2double PrimVar_j[MAXNVAR] = {0.0};
1366 su2double Secondary_j[MAXNVAR] = {0.0};
1367 su2double Residual[MAXNVAR] = {0.0};
1368 su2double** Jacobian_i = new su2double*[nVar];
1369 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Jacobian_i[iVar] = new su2double[nVar];
1370
1371 su2double weight;
1372 su2double P_static, rho_static;
1373
1374 for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
1375 if (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == FLUID_INTERFACE) {
1376 SU2_OMP_FOR_DYN(OMP_MIN_SIZE)
1377 for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
1378 iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
1379
1380 if (geometry->nodes->GetDomain(iPoint)) {
1381 nDonorVertex = GetnSlidingStates(iMarker, iVertex);
1382
1383 /*--- Initialize Residual, this will serve to accumulate the average ---*/
1384
1385 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
1386 Residual[iVar] = 0.0;
1387 for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++) Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] = 0.0;
1388 }
1389
1390 /*--- Loop over the nDonorVertexes and compute the averaged flux ---*/
1391
1392 for (jVertex = 0; jVertex < nDonorVertex; jVertex++) {
1393 Point_Normal = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
1394
1395 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++) {
1396 PrimVar_i[iVar] = nodes->GetPrimitive(iPoint, iVar);
1397 PrimVar_j[iVar] = GetSlidingState(iMarker, iVertex, iVar, jVertex);
1398 }
1399
1400 /*--- Get the weight computed in the interpolator class for the j-th donor vertex ---*/
1401
1402 weight = GetSlidingState(iMarker, iVertex, nPrimVar, jVertex);
1403
1404 /*--- Set primitive variables ---*/
1405
1406 conv_numerics->SetPrimitive(PrimVar_i, PrimVar_j);
1407
1408 if (FlowRegime == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE) {
1409 if (!(config->GetKind_FluidModel() == STANDARD_AIR || config->GetKind_FluidModel() == IDEAL_GAS)) {
1410 auto Secondary_i = nodes->GetSecondary(iPoint);
1411
1412 P_static = PrimVar_j[nDim + 1];
1413 rho_static = PrimVar_j[nDim + 2];
1414 GetFluidModel()->SetTDState_Prho(P_static, rho_static);
1415
1416 Secondary_j[0] = GetFluidModel()->GetdPdrho_e();
1417 Secondary_j[1] = GetFluidModel()->GetdPde_rho();
1418
1419 conv_numerics->SetSecondary(Secondary_i, Secondary_j);
1420 }
1421 }
1422
1423 /*--- Set the normal vector ---*/
1424
1425 geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
1426 for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
1427
1428 conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
1429
1430 if (dynamic_grid)
1431 conv_numerics->SetGridVel(geometry->nodes->GetGridVel(iPoint), geometry->nodes->GetGridVel(iPoint));
1432
1433 /*--- Compute the convective residual using an upwind scheme ---*/
1434
1435 auto residual = conv_numerics->ComputeResidual(config);
1436
1437 /*--- Accumulate the residuals to compute the average ---*/
1438
1439 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
1440 Residual[iVar] += weight * residual[iVar];
1441 for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++) Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] += weight * residual.jacobian_i[iVar][jVar];
1442 }
1443 }
1444
1445 /*--- Add Residuals and Jacobians ---*/
1446
1447 LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
1448
1449 if (implicit) Jacobian.AddBlock2Diag(iPoint, Jacobian_i);
1450
1451 if (viscous) {
1452 /*--- Initialize Residual, this will serve to accumulate the average ---*/
1453
1454 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
1455 Residual[iVar] = 0.0;
1456 for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++) Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] = 0.0;
1457 }
1458
1459 /*--- Loop over the nDonorVertexes and compute the averaged flux ---*/
1460
1461 for (jVertex = 0; jVertex < nDonorVertex; jVertex++) {
1462 PrimVar_j[nDim + 5] = GetSlidingState(iMarker, iVertex, nDim + 5, jVertex);
1463 PrimVar_j[nDim + 6] = GetSlidingState(iMarker, iVertex, nDim + 6, jVertex);
1464
1465 /*--- Get the weight computed in the interpolator class for the j-th donor vertex ---*/
1466
1467 weight = GetSlidingState(iMarker, iVertex, nPrimVar, jVertex);
1468
1469 /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
1470
1471 visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
1472 su2double Coord_Reflected[MAXNDIM];
1473 GeometryToolbox::PointPointReflect(nDim, geometry->nodes->GetCoord(Point_Normal),
1474 geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint), Coord_Reflected);
1475 visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint), Coord_Reflected);
1476
1477 /*--- Primitive variables, and gradient ---*/
1478
1479 visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(PrimVar_i, PrimVar_j);
1480 visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(nodes->GetGradient_Primitive(iPoint),
1481 nodes->GetGradient_Primitive(iPoint));
1482
1483 /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy ---*/
1484
1485 if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == TURB_MODEL::SST)
1486 visc_numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(solver_container[TURB_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(iPoint, 0),
1487 solver_container[TURB_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(iPoint, 0));
1488
1489 /*--- Compute and update residual ---*/
1490
1491 auto residual = visc_numerics->ComputeResidual(config);
1492
1493 /*--- Accumulate the residuals to compute the average ---*/
1494
1495 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
1496 Residual[iVar] += weight * residual[iVar];
1497 for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++) Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] += weight * residual.jacobian_i[iVar][jVar];
1498 }
1499 }
1500
1501 LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
1502
1503 /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
1504
1505 if (implicit) Jacobian.SubtractBlock2Diag(iPoint, Jacobian_i);
1506 }
1507 }
1508 }
1509 END_SU2_OMP_FOR
1510 }
1511 }
1512
1513 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) delete[] Jacobian_i[iVar];
1514 delete[] Jacobian_i;
1515}

1517template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
1518void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::BC_Custom(CGeometry* geometry, CSolver** solver_container, CNumerics* conv_numerics,
1519 CNumerics* visc_numerics, CConfig* config, unsigned short val_marker) {
1520 /* Check for a verification solution. */
1521
1522 if (VerificationSolution) {
1523 unsigned short iVar;
1524 unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, total_index;
1525
1526 bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
1527
1528 /*--- Get the physical time. ---*/
1529
1530 su2double time = 0.0;
1531 if (config->GetTime_Marching() != TIME_MARCHING::STEADY) time = config->GetPhysicalTime();
1532
1533 /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker ---*/
1534
1535 SU2_OMP_FOR_STAT(OMP_MIN_SIZE)
1536 for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
1537 /*--- Get the point index for the current node. ---*/
1538
1539 iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
1540
1541 /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e, not a halo node) ---*/
1542
1543 if (geometry->nodes->GetDomain(iPoint)) {
1544 /*--- Get the coordinates for the current node. ---*/
1545
1546 const su2double* coor = geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint);
1547
1548 /*--- Get the conservative state from the verification solution. ---*/
1549
1550 su2double Solution[MAXNVAR] = {0.0};
1551 VerificationSolution->GetBCState(coor, time, Solution);
1552
1553 /*--- For verification cases, we will apply a strong Dirichlet
1554 condition by setting the solution values at the boundary nodes
1555 directly and setting the residual to zero at those nodes. ---*/
1556
1557 nodes->SetSolution_Old(iPoint, Solution);
1558 nodes->SetSolution(iPoint, Solution);
1559 nodes->SetRes_TruncErrorZero(iPoint);
1560 LinSysRes.SetBlock_Zero(iPoint);
1561
1562 /*--- Adjust rows of the Jacobian (includes 1 in the diagonal) ---*/
1563
1564 if (implicit) {
1565 for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
1566 total_index = iPoint * nVar + iVar;
1567 Jacobian.DeleteValsRowi(total_index);
1568 }
1569 }
1570 }
1571 }
1572 END_SU2_OMP_FOR
1573
1574 } else {
1575 /* The user must specify the custom BC's here. */
1576 SU2_MPI::Error("Implement customized boundary conditions here.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1577 }
1578}

1580template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
1581void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::EdgeFluxResidual(const CGeometry *geometry,
1582 const CSolver* const* solvers,
1583 CConfig *config) {
1584 if (!edgeNumerics) {
1585 if (!ReducerStrategy && (omp_get_max_threads() > 1) &&
1586 (config->GetEdgeColoringGroupSize() % Double::Size != 0)) {
1587 SU2_MPI::Error("When using vectorization, the EDGE_COLORING_GROUP_SIZE must be divisible "
1588 "by the SIMD length (2, 4, or 8).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1589 }
1590 InstantiateEdgeNumerics(solvers, config);
1591 }
1592
1593 /*--- Non-physical counter. ---*/
1594 unsigned long counterLocal = 0;
1595 SU2_OMP_MASTER
1596 ErrorCounter = 0;
1597 END_SU2_OMP_MASTER
1598
1599 /*--- For hybrid parallel AD, pause preaccumulation if there is shared reading of
1600 * variables, otherwise switch to the faster adjoint evaluation mode. ---*/
1601 bool pausePreacc = false;
1602 if (ReducerStrategy) pausePreacc = AD::PausePreaccumulation();
1603 else AD::StartNoSharedReading();
1604
1605 /*--- Loop over edge colors. ---*/
1606 for (auto color : EdgeColoring) {
1607 /*--- Chunk size is at least OMP_MIN_SIZE and a multiple of the color group size. ---*/
1608 SU2_OMP_FOR_DYN(nextMultiple(OMP_MIN_SIZE, color.groupSize))
1609 for(auto k = 0ul; k < color.size; k += Double::Size) {
1610 Int iEdge;
1611 Double mask;
1612 for (auto j = 0ul; j < Double::Size; ++j) {
1613 bool in = (k+j < color.size);
1614 mask[j] = in;
1615 iEdge[j] = color.indices[k+j*in];
1616 }
1617
1618 if (ReducerStrategy) {
1619 edgeNumerics->ComputeFlux(iEdge, *config, *geometry, *nodes, UpdateType::REDUCTION, mask, EdgeFluxes, Jacobian);
1620 } else {
1621 edgeNumerics->ComputeFlux(iEdge, *config, *geometry, *nodes, UpdateType::COLORING, mask, LinSysRes, Jacobian);
1622 }
1623 if (MGLevel == MESH_0) {
1624 for (auto j = 0ul; j < Double::Size; ++j)
1625 counterLocal += (nodes->NonPhysicalEdgeCounter[iEdge[j]] > 0);
1626 }
1627 }
1628 END_SU2_OMP_FOR
1629 }
1630
1631 FinalizeResidualComputation(geometry, pausePreacc, counterLocal, config);
1632}
1633
1634template <class V, ENUM_REGIME R>
1635void CFVMFlowSolverBase<V, R>::SumEdgeFluxes(const CGeometry* geometry) {
1636
1637 SU2_OMP_FOR_STAT(omp_chunk_size)
1638 for (unsigned long iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPoint; ++iPoint) {
1639
1640 LinSysRes.SetBlock_Zero(iPoint);
1641
1642 for (auto iEdge : geometry->nodes->GetEdges(iPoint)) {
1643 if (iPoint == geometry->edges->GetNode(iEdge,0))
1644 LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, EdgeFluxes.GetBlock(iEdge));
1645 else
1646 LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, EdgeFluxes.GetBlock(iEdge));
1647 }
1648 }
1649 END_SU2_OMP_FOR
1650}
